Package soot

Class SootMethodRefImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • soot.SootMethodRefImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SootMethodInterface, SootMethodRef
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PolymorphicMethodRef
    public class SootMethodRefImpl
extends Object
implements SootMethodRef
    Representation of a reference to a method as it appears in a class file. Note that the method directly referred to may not actually exist; the actual target of the reference is determined according to the resolution procedure in the Java Virtual Machine Specification, 2nd ed, section 5.4.3.3.
    Author:
    Manuel Benz 22.10.19 - Delegate method resolution behavior to FastHierarchy to have one common place for extension

      • tryResolve

        public SootMethod tryResolve()
        Description copied from interface: SootMethodRef
        Tries to resolve this method call, i.e., tries to finds the method to which this reference points. This method does not handle virtual dispatch, it just gives the immediate target, which can also be an abstract method. This method is different from SootMethodRef.resolve() in the following ways: (1) This method does not fail when the target method does not exist and phantom references are not allowed. In that case, it returns null. (2) While SootMethodRef.resolve() creates fake methods that throw exceptions when a target method does not exist and phantom references are allowed, this method returns null.
        Specified by:
        tryResolve in interface SootMethodRef
        Returns:
        The immediate target if this method reference if available, null otherwise
